</section>
<section class="section section--alt section-cards">
  <div class="section-content">
    <h2 style="font-weight: 700;">What We Do</h2>
  <p style="max-width: 780px; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 500;">
    First Step Fire Protection specializes in the application of long-term
    wildfire retardants using the same active ingredients trusted by the
    U.S. Forest Service. Our work focuses on targeted, high-impact treatments
    that slow fire spread, reduce ignition potential, and buy critical time
    during wildfire events.
  </p>

  <div
    style="
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
    "
  >
    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">Residential Perimeter Protection</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        Application of long-term fire retardants around homes and structures to
        create defensible perimeters designed to resist ember intrusion and
        surface fire spread throughout fire season.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/residential-boarder.png"
        alt="Residential Perimeter Protection"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; margin-top: 1rem;"
      />
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">Critical Infrastructure Protection</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        Targeted retardant treatments around communication towers, substations,
        pump stations, and other essential assets where continuity of operation
        is critical during wildfire events.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/critical-boarder.png"
        alt="Critical Infrastructure Hardening"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; margin-top: 1rem;"
      />
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">Roadway/Evacuation Protection</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        Strategic application of long-term retardants along roadways and
        evacuation routes to reduce roadside ignition risk and improve safety
        for evacuation and emergency response.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/evacuation-boarder.png"
        alt="Evacuation Corridor Protection"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; margin-top: 1rem;"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <img
    src="/images/sprayer-icon-right.png"
    alt=""
    class="sprayer-icon-left"
  />
</section>
<section class="section section-cards">
  <h2 style="font-size: 2.3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700;">
    How It Works
  </h2>

  <p style="max-width: 780px; margin-bottom: 3rem; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 500;">
    First Step Fire Protection delivers wildfire mitigation through a clear,
    repeatable process designed to reduce risk, support decision-making, and
    create defensible records of work performed.
  </p>

  <div
    style="
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 2.5rem;
    "
  >
    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">1. Assess</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        We evaluate site-specific wildfire exposure based on asset type,
        surrounding fuels, access, and operational priorities. Assessments are
        tailored to homes, infrastructure, and evacuation corridors rather than
        one-size-fits-all treatments.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/red-check-box.jpg"
        alt="Check box"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 56%; margin: 1rem auto 0 auto;"
      />
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">2. Mitigate</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        Long-term fire retardants are applied strategically using products with
        the same active ingredients trusted by the U.S. Forest Service, adapted
        for residential and infrastructure protection throughout fire season.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/red-check-box.jpg"
        alt="Check box"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 56%; margin: 1rem auto 0 auto;"
      />
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 700;">3. Document</h3>
      <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 500;">
        Every long term retardant treatment is mapped, time-stamped, and documented using First Fire
        Map, creating a clear visual record of mitigation efforts that can be
        reviewed by property owners, agencies, and partners.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/images/red-check-box.jpg"
        alt="Check box"
        style="width: 100%; height: auto; max-width: 56%; margin: 1rem auto 0 auto;"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <img
    src="/images/sprayer-icon-right.png"
    alt=""
    class="sprayer-icon-top-right"
  />

  <img
    src="/images/sprayer-icon-right.png"
    alt=""
    class="sprayer-icon-bottom-left"
  />
</section>
<section class="section">
  <h2 style="font-size: 2.3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-align: center;">
    Built for Accountability. Designed for Defensible Records.
  </h2>

  <p style="max-width: 800px; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
    Wildfire mitigation only matters if it can be verified, reviewed, and
    maintained over time. First Step Fire Protection documents every treatment
    spatially and operationally, creating clear records of what was done, where
    it was done, and when it was performed.
  </p>

  <p style="max-width: 800px; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 500; text-align: center; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
    Our work is supported by <strong>First Fire Map</strong>, a wildfire
    mitigation mapping and documentation platform designed to provide visibility
    for property owners, agencies, insurers, and decision-makers. Treatments are
    mapped to real-world assets and locations, creating a living record that
    supports planning, reporting, and accountability.  (See Below)
  </p>

  <div
    style="
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    "
  >
    <img
      src="/images/FFMexampleGraphic.png"
      alt="First Fire Map Example"
      style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
    />
    <img
